[1] Liberia: new case, sexual transmission suspected
Date: 25 Mar 2015
Source: Yahoo [edited]
http://news.yahoo.com/liberia-says-1st-ebola-patient-month-isolated-case-144722606.html


A Liberian woman who last week became the country's 1st Ebola patient in more than one month has not passed on the infection to anyone else, a senior official said Wed 25 Mar 2015. The case was a setback to hopes that Liberia, once the worst Ebola-hit country, would soon be officially declared free of the deadly disease.

"The patient is in a stable condition. She is responding to treatment," said Francis Karteh, the head of Liberia's Ebola Incident Management Team. "She had contact with more than 50 people. We have been following these people, and they are all home with no sign of Ebola yet." The woman is the wife of a cured Ebola patient, a source said. [at present they are speculating the husband may have infected her through sexual intercourse after returning home, but there is no documentation of this. A very good article describing this case and some of the investigations can be found at http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/25/world/africa/exposure-concerns-grow-in-liberia-after-diagnosis-of-first-ebola-case-in-weeks.html?hpw&rref=health&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&module=well-regionÂ®ion=bottom-well&WT.nav=bottom-well. - Mod.MPP]

[See related stories below and in [5]. - Mod.JW]

--
25 Mar 2015: Liberia says 1st Ebola patient in a month is isolated case
http://medicalxpress.com/news/2015-03-liberia-ebola-patient-month-isolated.html
["A Liberian woman who last week became the country's 1st Ebola patient in more than one month has not passed on the infection to anyone else, a senior official said Wed 25 Mar 2015."]

25 Mar 2015: Liberia reports 2 new Ebola cases [in addition to the case above]
http://www.aa.com.tr/en/rss/483684--liberia-reports-2-new-ebola-cases
[Total new cases: 3. One of the 2 cases involved an 18-year-old girl who was taking care of her 44-year-old mother who recently tested positive for the virus. The 2nd new case is a young man whose girlfriend is said to be involved in cross-border trade from the New Kru Town community (town in a suburb of Liberia's capital, Monrovia). Contact tracers are still trying to convince the young man to reveal his contacts. He was discovered to have Ebola after being seen in the Clara Town area vomiting blood, following which he was taken to the Ebola treatment unit.]
[The senior official quoted above was not necessarily wrong; no connection has been traced between the 1st patient and these 2 new ones. - Mod.JW]

