[5] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

23 Mar 2015 Guinea: Suspected killers of Ebola workers in Guinea go on trial
http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/ebola-virus-outbreak/suspected-killers-ebola-workers-go-trial-n328456
[Approximately 78 suspects are being tried in the town of N'Nzerekore, 900 km (560 miles) from the capital of Conakry for killing 8 Ebola health workers and journalists.]

20 Mar 2015 Guinea: Spike in Ebola in Guinea could reflect access to hidden patients
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503210142.html
[According to a senior World Health Organization official, the latest spike in Guinea's Ebola cases could indicate aid teams are at last gaining access to hidden patients rather than a surge of new cases. It also explains why most new cases are not linked to contacts under follow-up.]

23 Mar 2015 Liberia: Ebola psychosocial counseling for residents of crematorium neighborhood
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503231804.html?viewall=1

23 Mar 2015 Liberia: 86 Persons quarantined in new Ebola virus emergence
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503231925.html?viewall=1
[86 quarantined in new (index) Ebola patient's house; over 100 contacts; 2000 students at risk as index patient had contact (selling food to staff, students, others). One of the schools is "within a stone's throw" from patient's residence, has 70 students who share one bathroom. Patient's daughter, who provided care to her mother as her condition worsened, attends a local school. One quarantined female contact said she was sending her children to school on Monday [23 Mar 2014] despite instructions from contact tracers not to do so. Male sexual contact (possibly the source of index patient's transmission) is reported by neighbors to have relocated to Freeport, Monrovia.]

23 Mar 2015 Liberia: Complacency responsible for new Ebola case in Liberia
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503231158.html?viewall=1

23 Mar 2015 Liberia: International partners visit latest Ebola victim's home
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503231204.html?viewall=1
[A team of international partners, consisting of representatives of the US Centers for Disease Control, World Health Organization, United
Nations Children's Fund, the Liberian Health Ministry and the More Than Me Institute, visited the home of the latest Ebola case (on the outskirts of Monrovia) to solicit information on how she contracted Ebola. The patient has been admitted to the MSF-run ELWA Ebola Treatment Unit (near Monrovia).]

23 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: A year after Ebola discovered, relapses seen in fight to end it
http://www.trust.org/item/20150323160144-jjyw7/
[Issues include mistakes in hospitals, lapses in basic measures for infection control (resulting in infection in 3 doctors in Guinea), and lack of vigilance. Cross-border transmission seen as a weak point: After more than USD 2 billion in aid and the deaths of more than 10 200 people in West Africa, the same mistakes are resurfacing. seeks to crack down on complacency.]

23 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: Hunters breaking an Ebola ban on bushmeat
http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-31985826
[Scientists have warned that bushmeat (non-domesticated forest animals hunted for human consumption) is probably the natural reservoir of the Ebola virus. Yet questions remain on the efficacy of the Ebola ban.]

23 Mar 2015 UK: Ebola: Northeast patients still undergoing treatment as world marks anniversary of outbreak
http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/news/north-east-news/ebola-north-east-patients-still-8899314
[Three healthcare workers are still under observation at Royal Victoria Infirmary, Newcastle, following exposure to Ebola while working in Sierra Leone. They will remain under observation until the 21-day period is over]

